    "body": "Been looking a bit to it, the code is really advanced. I might have an idea. The parsing seems to be fine but somehow the comments are written after the `MemberAccess` inner stuff (msg. or block.) in the formatting part probably\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n[fmt/src/formatter.rs:1209] &chunks = [\r\n    Chunk {\r\n        postfixes_before: [],\r\n        prefixes: [\r\n            CommentWithMetadata {\r\n                ty: Line,\r\n                loc: File(\r\n                    0,\r\n                    114,\r\n                    134,\r\n                ),\r\n                has_newline_before: false,\r\n                indent_len: 12,\r\n                comment: \"// This is a comment\",\r\n                position: Prefix,\r\n            },\r\n        ],\r\n        content: \"value\",\r\n        postfixes: [],\r\n        needs_space: None,\r\n    },\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/master/fmt/src/formatter.rs#L1188-L1216\r\n\r\nMy code editing tools are broken with the formatting part, looks like it's grabbing a lot of foundry packages and rust-analyzer allocates way too much CPU on my machine and make it crash.\r\nHope to find the culprit tmr!",
